{"id":"anim-250","category":"motion_principles","difficulty":"expert","platform":"both","title":"Final: Motion as craft","design_intent":"Animation is craft — invisible when good, painful when bad. Treat with same rigor as code.","reference_inspiration":"Apple, Linear, Stripe — they invest in motion as first-class.","anti_patterns_to_avoid":["Animation as decoration only","Skipping reduced-motion","Same easing for all moods","No motion design system","Animating without measuring perf","Lose accessibility for aesthetics"],"motion_reasoning":"Senior thinking:\n1. Every motion communicates — make it intentional.\n2. Match easing/duration to emotional context.\n3. Compositor-only properties: transform + opacity.\n4. Reduced motion = graceful alternative, not absence.\n5. Test on slow devices.\n6. Build a motion system: tokens for duration, ease, spring.\n7. Document the WHY behind each animation.\n8. Audit periodically — motion that lost its purpose should be removed.\n9. Motion is craft — treat with same rigor as the code that powers it.","performance_strategy":{"what_animates":"transform + opacity by default; avoid layout properties","thread_management":"Off main thread when possible","gpu_considerations":"Stable will-change; avoid layer churn","interrupt_handling":"Interruptible animations preferred"},"accessibility":{"reduced_motion":"Always provide alternative","screen_reader":"Don't break announcements with motion","vestibular_safety":"Bounded translations; no heavy parallax"},"solution":"// docs/MOTION_PHILOSOPHY.md\n/*\n## Motion principles\n\n1. **Intent first** — every animation answers a 'why'\n2. **Communicate, don't decorate** — motion that doesn't communicate is noise\n3. **Compositor-only** — transform + opacity; no layout properties\n4. **Bounded** — short for routine, longer reserved for hero moments\n5. **Match the moment** — settle for serious, snap for confirmation, spring for play\n6. **Respect the user** — prefers-reduced-motion is non-negotiable\n7. **Test on cheap devices** — 60fps on $200 Android or it's not done\n8. **System over snowflakes** — tokens for duration, easing, spring physics\n9. **Audit regularly** — animations that lost purpose get retired\n10. **Craft** — motion is the difference between an app that works and an app that delights\n*/\n\n// motion-system.ts\nexport const DURATION = {instant: 0.15, routine: 0.25, deliberate: 0.4, hero: 0.8};\nexport const EASING = {\n  settle: [0.4, 0, 0.2, 1],\n  snap: [0.25, 0.46, 0.45, 0.94],\n  emphasized: [0.2, 0, 0, 1]\n};\nexport const SPRING = {\n  gentle: {type: 'spring', damping: 30, stiffness: 200},\n  snappy: {type: 'spring', damping: 20, stiffness: 400},\n  bouncy: {type: 'spring', damping: 12, stiffness: 300}\n};","interaction_details":["Every team member uses the same tokens","Motion reviews like code reviews","Reduced motion validated per release","Performance budgeted per page"],"what_breaks_naive_approach":"Motion as afterthought: inconsistent feel; performance issues; accessibility complaints. With discipline: motion becomes a competitive moat — apps feel premium, fast, considerate. Users may not articulate why, but they FEEL it."}
